âœ… FACT TABLES (Transactional Facts)

These represent business events and contain foreign keys + measures.

1. fact_sales_orders

From bronze.sales_orders
Keys:

sale_id

customer_id (FK dim_customers)

product_id (FK dim_products)

sale_date (FK dim_time)

Measures:

quantity

total_price

payment_method

2. fact_project_bugs

From bronze.project_bug_reports
Keys:

bug_id

project_id (FK dim_projects)

reported_date (FK dim_time)

Measures:

severity

resolved (0/1)

3. fact_employee_performance

From bronze.employee_performance
Keys:

perf_id

employee_id (FK dim_employees)

month + year (FK dim_time or make date_from_parts)

Measures:

tasks_completed

overtime_hours

performance_score

project_success_rate

4. fact_candidate_interviews

From bronze.candidate_interviews
Keys:

interview_id

candidate_id (FK dim_candidates)

recruiter_id (can FK dim_employees if recruiters are employees)

Measures:

interview_score

stage

result

5. fact_candidate_cv

From bronze.candidate_cv_raw
Keys:

cv_id

candidate_id

Measures:

parsed_keywords count

text length

language_detected

(This is a semi-structured fact table, used for NLP analytics.)

